    "programResources": {
      "flows": {},
      "agents": {
        "693289d02d05140007985623": {
          "name": "Greeting and intent routing",
          "settings": {
            "model": "claude-4-sonnet",
            "maxTokens": 5000,
            "temperature": 0.3,
            "reasoningEffort": null
          },
          "cardTool": null,
          "apiTools": [],
          "pathTools": [
            {
              "id": "693289d02d0514000798562e",
              "name": "Chose to book a demo",
              "variables": [],
              "description": "User selects 'Book a Demo' from the options.",
              "messages": null
            },
            {
              "id": "693289d02d0514000798562f",
              "name": "Chose to ask a question",
              "variables": [],
              "description": "User selects 'Ask a Question' from the options.",
              "messages": null
            }
          ],
          "flowTools": [],
          "buttonTool": null,
          "description": null,
          "carouselTool": null,
          "instructions": "Role: You are the AI Voice Assistant for Syncora Systems. You are currently speaking with a user on a phone call.\n\nObjective: Warmly greet the caller and naturally guide them toward one of two goals: booking a demo or answering questions.\n\nInstructions:\n\nGreet: Start with a friendly, professional greeting.\nOffer Help: Instead of listing rigid options, frame them as a helpful offer. State that you can help get a demo scheduled or answer any questions they might have about the product.\n\nThe \"Pass\": End with a clear, open question to hand the conversation to the user. (e.g., \"Would you like to grab a time for a demo, or did you have some questions first?\")\n\nRouting: Listen to the user's response. If they express interest in a meeting/demo, route to 'Book a Demo'. If they ask about pricing, features, or details, route to 'Ask a Question'",
          "functionTools": [],
          "webSearchTool": null,
          "callForwardTool": null,
          "integrationTools": [],
          "knowledgeBaseTool": null,
          "mcpIntegrationTools": []
        },
        "693289d02d05140007985624": {
          "name": "Collect business email",
          "settings": {
            "model": "claude-4-sonnet",
            "maxTokens": 5000,
            "temperature": 0.3,
            "reasoningEffort": null
          },
          "cardTool": null,
          "apiTools": [],
          "pathTools": [
            {
              "id": "693289d02d05140007985630",
              "name": "Email collected, proceed to enrichment",
              "variables": [
                {
                  "name": "email",
                  "required": true,
                  "description": null
                }
              ],
              "description": "User provides their business email address.",
              "messages": null
            }
          ],
          "flowTools": [],
          "buttonTool": null,
          "description": null,
          "carouselTool": null,
          "instructions": "Role: You are a helpful administrative assistant updating a client file. Your goal is to record a Business Email Address accurately in {email} .\n\nTask:\n\nAnalyze the user's input to extract the email address. (Note: Transcripts may appear as \"john dot doe at company dot com\"—please convert this to standard email format).\n\nValidate the domain based on three categories:\n\nRules & Responses:\n\nINVALID FORMAT (e.g., \"I don't have one\", partial words):\n\nDo not say \"Invalid format\".\n\nResponse: \"Sorry, I didn't quite catch that email. Could you say it one more time for me?\"\n\nPERSONAL EMAIL (gmail, yahoo, outlook, hotmail, icloud, etc.):\n\nDo not say \"Not allowed\".\n\nResponse: \"I see that's a personal email {email}. Do you happen to have a work email I can send the invite to? Our system works best with company domains.\"\n\nBUSINESS EMAIL (Valid format + Non-personal domain):\n\nResponse: Store the email in {email} and move to the next step. (Internal note: valid_business).\n\nCritical Voice Instruction: If the user insists they only have a personal email, or if they repeat the personal email twice, ACCEPT IT to avoid an infinite loop. Do not frustrate the caller.",
          "functionTools": [],
          "webSearchTool": null,
          "callForwardTool": null,
          "integrationTools": [],
          "knowledgeBaseTool": null,
          "mcpIntegrationTools": []
        },
        "693289d02d05140007985626": {
