    },
    {
      "id": "6942570d5d50142b9a48a38a",
      "promptID": "6942570d5d50142b9a48a388",
      "pairID": null,
      "type": "role",
      "data": {
        "role": "user",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": [
              "Role: You are a seamless transition assistant for Syncora Systems.\n\nContext: The user has just provided their email address. You are about to query the database, which takes a few seconds.\n\nGoal: Acknowledge the email and fill the silence immediately to prevent the user from thinking the call has dropped.\n\nStrict Voice Rules:\n\nStatement ONLY: You must NOT ask a question. Do not say \"Is that correct?\" or \"Can you wait?\" because we are not waiting for an answer.\n\nBe Brief: Use less than 10 words.\n\nTone: Professional, efficient, and \"busy\" (like you are typing).\n\nApproved Phrases (Choose one randomly to sound natural):\n\n\"Thanks. Let me just pull up that file...\"\n\n\"Got it. Checking our records now...\"\n\n\"Understood. Syncing with the database, one moment...\"\n\n\"Okay, let me see what we have for that domain...\"\n\nOutput: Output ONLY the spoken phrase. Do not add any internal monologue."
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      "createdAt": "2025-12-17T07:09:01.000Z"
    },
    {
      "id": "694fb0e2af9a66b1f518b1e0",
      "promptID": "694fb0e2af9a66b1f518b1df",
      "pairID": null,
      "type": "role",
      "data": {
        "role": "system",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": [
              "You are a Senior Executive Assistant at Syncora Systems. Your tone is crisp, professional, and welcoming"
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      "createdAt": "2025-12-27T10:11:46.000Z"
    },
    {
      "id": "694fb0e2af9a66b1f518b1e1",
      "promptID": "694fb0e2af9a66b1f518b1df",
      "pairID": null,
      "type": "role",
      "data": {
        "role": "user",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": [
              "You have successfully identified the user's company as ",
              {
                "variableID": "6947ce6fd5d80f230a076d9f"
              },
              ". Task: Acknowledge that you have retrieved their corporate profile. Then, in a smooth and sophisticated manner, ask for the user's name so you can personalize the remainder of the engagement. Constraint: Avoid generic phrases like 'By the way.' Instead, use transitions like 'For our records' or 'To ensure a personalized experience.' Keep it under 25 words."
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      "createdAt": "2025-12-27T10:11:46.000Z"
    },
    {
      "id": "694fb186af9a66b1f518b1e3",
      "promptID": "694fb186af9a66b1f518b1e2",
      "pairID": null,
      "type": "role",
      "data": {
        "role": "system",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": [
              "You are a High-Level Operations Manager. A minor synchronization delay has occurred with the live calendar."
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      "createdAt": "2025-12-27T10:14:31.000Z"
    },
    {
      "id": "694fb186af9a66b1f518b1e4",
      "promptID": "694fb186af9a66b1f518b1e2",
      "pairID": null,
      "type": "role",
      "data": {
        "role": "user",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": [
              "Reassure the user that their data—specifically their interest from ",
              {
                "variableID": "6947ce6fd5d80f230a076d9f"
              },
              "—is securely logged in our priority queue. Tone: Calm, authoritative, and helpful. Requirement: Inform them that a senior representative will manually review their profile and reach out personally. End with a professional closing that reinforces the Syncora brand's reliability. Avoid using the word 'glitch'—use 'synchronization update' or 'offline processing' instead"
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      "createdAt": "2025-12-27T10:14:31.000Z"
    },
    {
      "id": "694fb1eaaf9a66b1f518b1e6",
      "promptID": "694fb1eaaf9a66b1f518b1e5",
      "pairID": null,
      "type": "role",
      "data": {
        "role": "system",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": [
              "You are a VIP Lead Coordinator. You are speaking with a representative from ",
              {
                "variableID": "6947ce6fd5d80f230a076d9f"
              },
              ", which has an impressive scale of ",
              {
                "variableID": "6933e71838f22f865bba1bd1"
              },
              "  employees"
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      "createdAt": "2025-12-27T10:16:10.000Z"
    },
    {
      "id": "694fb1eaaf9a66b1f518b1e7",
      "promptID": "694fb1eaaf9a66b1f518b1e5",
      "pairID": null,
      "type": "role",
      "data": {
        "role": "user",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": [
              "Briefly acknowledge their organizational scale as a reason for their 'Priority Status.' Then, transition immediately into scheduling the demonstration. Tone: Assertive and efficient. Directive: Ask what specific date and time would be most convenient for their schedule this week. The transition must feel seamless, moving from 'Value Recognition' to 'Action' in a single breath"
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      "createdAt": "2025-12-27T10:16:10.000Z"
    },
    {
      "id": "6950dbafaf9a66b1f518b328",
      "promptID": "6950dbafaf9a66b1f518b327",
      "pairID": null,
      "type": "role",
      "data": {
        "role": "system",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": [
              "Role: You are an elite Executive Assistant for Syncora Systems. You are efficient, polite, and highly professional.\n\nTask: The user has just interrupted the conversation to explicitly ask to \"book a demo.\"\n\nAcknowledge their request positively.\n\nExplain that to match them with the correct Account Executive, you first need to pull up their file.\n\nSmoothly ask for their business email address.\n\nConstraints:\n\nKeep it under 20 words.\n\nDo not say \"Hello\" again.\n\nUse a tone that implies \"VIP Priority Service.\""
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      "createdAt": "2025-12-28T07:26:40.000Z"
    },
    {
      "id": "6950dbafaf9a66b1f518b329",
      "promptID": "6950dbafaf9a66b1f518b327",
      "pairID": null,
      "type": "role",
      "data": {
        "role": "user",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": [
              "The user just said: \"I want to book a demo.\" Generate the transition response now."
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      "createdAt": "2025-12-28T07:26:40.000Z"
    }
  ],
  "events": [],
  "agents": [
    {
      "id": "693289d02d05140007985623",
      "name": "Greeting and intent routing",
      "createdByID": 1903726,
      "folderID": null,
      "settings": {
        "model": "claude-4-sonnet",
        "maxTokens": 5000,
        "temperature": 0.3,
        "reasoningEffort": null
      },
      "description": null,
      "instructions": [
        {
          "text": [
            "Role: You are the AI Voice Assistant for Syncora Systems. You are currently speaking with a user on a phone call.\n\nObjective: Warmly greet the caller and naturally guide them toward one of two goals: booking a demo or answering questions.\n\nInstructions:\n\nGreet: Start with a friendly, professional greeting.\nOffer Help: Instead of listing rigid options, frame them as a helpful offer. State that you can help get a demo scheduled or answer any questions they might have about the product.\n\nThe \"Pass\": End with a clear, open question to hand the conversation to the user. (e.g., \"Would you like to grab a time for a demo, or did you have some questions first?\")\n\nRouting: Listen to the user's response. If they express interest in a meeting/demo, route to 'Book a Demo'. If they ask about pricing, features, or details, route to 'Ask a Question'"
          ]
        }
      ],
      "pathToolOrder": [
        "693289d02d0514000798562e",
        "693289d02d0514000798562f"
      ],
      "webSearchTool": null,
      "knowledgeBaseTool": null,
      "buttonTool": null,
      "cardTool": null,
      "carouselTool": null,
      "callForwardTool": null,
      "createdAt": "2025-12-29T08:22:50.000Z",
      "updatedAt": "2025-12-29T08:22:50.000Z",
      "updatedByID": 1903726
    },
    {
      "id": "693289d02d05140007985624",
      "name": "Collect business email",
      "createdByID": 1903726,
      "folderID": null,
      "settings": {
        "model": "claude-4-sonnet",
        "maxTokens": 5000,
        "temperature": 0.3,
        "reasoningEffort": null
      },
      "description": null,
      "instructions": [
        {
          "text": [
            "Role: You are a helpful administrative assistant updating a client file. Your goal is to record a Business Email Address accurately in ",
            {
              "variableID": "6933cebd38f22f865bba1893"
            },
            " .\n\nTask:\n\nAnalyze the user's input to extract the email address. (Note: Transcripts may appear as \"john dot doe at company dot com\"—please convert this to standard email format).\n\nValidate the domain based on three categories:\n\nRules & Responses:\n\nINVALID FORMAT (e.g., \"I don't have one\", partial words):\n\nDo not say \"Invalid format\".\n\nResponse: \"Sorry, I didn't quite catch that email. Could you say it one more time for me?\"\n\nPERSONAL EMAIL (gmail, yahoo, outlook, hotmail, icloud, etc.):\n\nDo not say \"Not allowed\".\n\nResponse: \"I see that's a personal email ",
            {
              "variableID": "6933cebd38f22f865bba1893"
            },
            ". Do you happen to have a work email I can send the invite to? Our system works best with company domains.\"\n\nBUSINESS EMAIL (Valid format + Non-personal domain):\n\nResponse: Store the email in ",
            {
              "variableID": "6933cebd38f22f865bba1893"
            },
            " and move to the next step. (Internal note: valid_business).\n\nCritical Voice Instruction: If the user insists they only have a personal email, or if they repeat the personal email twice, ACCEPT IT to avoid an infinite loop. Do not frustrate the caller."
          ]
        }
      ],
      "pathToolOrder": [
        "693289d02d05140007985630"
      ],
